<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1262,1876]" box="[189,1388,1332,1356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Etymology. The specific name is taken after one of the collectors, Dr. Francesco Ballarin; name in genitive case.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1262,1876]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Diagnosis. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Deeleman-Reinhold, 1995" authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="1995" box="[629,1109,1366,1390]" class="Arachnida" family="Ochyroceratidae" genus="Speocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suratthaniensis">
<emphasis box="[629,820,1366,1390]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. suratthaniensis</emphasis>
Deeleman-Reinhold, 1995
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the greatly enlarged palpal tibia, the spherical palp and the wide embolus (
<figureCitation box="[890,1012,1401,1425]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-47@11.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Speocera ballarini Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, male. A. Left palp, prolateral view. B. Left palp, retrolateral view. C. Left palp, dorsal view. D. Left palp, retrolateral view, cleared in lactic acid. Scale bars=0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366939/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 8A–B</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="1995" box="[1030,1220,1401,1425]" class="Arachnida" family="Ochyroceratidae" genus="Speocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suratthaniensis">
<emphasis box="[1030,1220,1401,1425]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. suratthaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males have a slightly enlarged palpal tibia, a flattened palp and narrow embolus (Deeleman-Reinhold, 1995: fig. 292).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1262,1876]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Description. Male. Total length 0.90; carapace length 0.45; carapace width 0.38; abdomen length 0.43; abdomen width 0.30. Prosoma: carapace pyriform, narrowing gradually anteriorly; light yellow, suffused with purplish pattern (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1438,1505,1529]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="12.[155,218,1661,1683]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,732,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-395@12.[189,1398,732,1616]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 9. Speocera ballarini Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, male. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. Scale bars=0.30mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366941/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
); pars cephalica flat; fovea not visible. Sternum light yellow, suffused with purplish color, as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[1268,1353,1540,1564]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="12.[155,218,1661,1683]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,732,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-395@12.[189,1398,732,1616]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 9. Speocera ballarini Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, male. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. Scale bars=0.30mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366941/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
). Endites light yellow with serrula; labium light yellow. Clypeus nearly vertical; short. Chelicerae light yellow, long, laterally slightly excavated; promargin with a series of six teeth reaching the lamina; retromargin with two small denticles (
<figureCitation box="[1274,1374,1609,1633]" captionStart="Figure 55" captionStartId="70.[154,217,2026,2048]" captionTargetBox="[195,1398,233,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-90@70.[188,1398,233,2011]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="Figure 55. Male chelicerae of Speocera spp.A–E, G–H.Anterior view. F, I. Lateral view. A. S. amber Li &amp; Li sp. nov. B. S. ankalana Li &amp; Li sp. nov. C. S. bachma Li &amp; Li sp. nov. D. S. ballarini Li &amp; Li sp. nov. E–F. S. bawangling Li &amp; Li sp. nov. G. S. bukittinggi Li &amp; Li sp. nov. H–I. S. cucphuong Li &amp; Li sp. nov. Scale bars=0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367039" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367039/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 55D</figureCitation>
). Eyes: six contiguous eyes surrounded by black pigmentation, 
<collectionCode box="[719,774,1644,1667]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">PME</collectionCode>
smallest, 
<collectionCode box="[877,929,1644,1668]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">ALE</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[977,1025,1644,1667]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">PLE</collectionCode>
nearly subequal (
<figureCitation box="[1210,1294,1644,1668]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="12.[155,218,1661,1683]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,732,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-395@12.[189,1398,732,1616]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 9. Speocera ballarini Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, male. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. Scale bars=0.30mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366941/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
). Opisthosoma oval; purplish (
<figureCitation box="[300,385,1678,1702]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="12.[155,218,1661,1683]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,732,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-395@12.[189,1398,732,1616]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 9. Speocera ballarini Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, male. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. Scale bars=0.30mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366941" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366941/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
). Legs light yellow; leg lengths I 1.37 (0.37, 0.13, 0.33, 0.31, 0.23); 
<collectionCode box="[1127,1145,1679,1702]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">II</collectionCode>
1.82 (0.48, 0.17, 0.55, 0.36, 0.26); 
<collectionCode box="[206,235,1714,1737]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">III</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode box="[246,274,1714,1737]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">IV</collectionCode>
missing. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[490,556,1713,1737]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-47@11.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Speocera ballarini Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, male. A. Left palp, prolateral view. B. Left palp, retrolateral view. C. Left palp, dorsal view. D. Left palp, retrolateral view, cleared in lactic acid. Scale bars=0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366939/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Palpal femur long; palpal tibia greatly enlarged basally, as long as cymbium (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-47@11.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Speocera ballarini Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, male. A. Left palp, prolateral view. B. Left palp, retrolateral view. C. Left palp, dorsal view. D. Left palp, retrolateral view, cleared in lactic acid. Scale bars=0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366939/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 8A–B</figureCitation>
). Cymbium conical, with long prolateral extension basally (
<figureCitation box="[844,929,1748,1772]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-47@11.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Speocera ballarini Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, male. A. Left palp, prolateral view. B. Left palp, retrolateral view. C. Left palp, dorsal view. D. Left palp, retrolateral view, cleared in lactic acid. Scale bars=0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366939/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Bulb spherical, as long as wide. Embolus long, wide, dark and basally with a short associated sclerite; sperm duct initially wide, gradually narrowing distally (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1405,1782,1806]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetId="figure-47@11.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Speocera ballarini Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, male. A. Left palp, prolateral view. B. Left palp, retrolateral view. C. Left palp, dorsal view. D. Left palp, retrolateral view, cleared in lactic acid. Scale bars=0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366939" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366939/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1262,1876]" box="[189,394,1817,1841]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1262,1876]" box="[189,707,1852,1876]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
